<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-15T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-15T07:00:00-05:00" n="79" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.01/99</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-15T20:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1916, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Bitter factional struggle Kwangtung; Chekiang quiet. In Peking Vice
                            President and Yuan cooperate. They contemplate joint action. Governors
                            asking the President to withdraw. The latter is looking for suitable man
                            to form coalition Cabinet, thus far in vain.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>